		<div class="col7 last">
		<p>Urinalysis is an important tool in disease detection, as well as monitoring and screening health. Abnormalities can be indicative of diseases of the urinary system as well as other organ systems, including liver function, and carbohydrate metabolism. Chemical evaluation of urine can be measured using commercially available in house dipstick tests. The app currently works with MultistixÂ® 10 SG Reagent Strips. The strips can perform analyses on blood, bilirubin, glucose, ketones, pH, protein, specific gravity, urobilinogen, leukocytes, and nitrite.</p>
		</div>
	
